  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women&apos;s Right to Protection and Participation for Equality and Peace Around Artisanal Mines in South Kivu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this project is to combat the marginalization of women in the different stages of mineral exploitation in the Democratic Republic of Congo, through the empowerment of women and their active participation in dialogues between different actors, in conflict prevention and in peacebuilding. In particular, this project aims to strengthen the integration of women into local natural resource management mechanisms and mining cooperatives, so that they are active members and participate in discussions and decision-making regarding mining. The implementation is taking into account the capacities of public and private institutions working in growth sectors that are still not sufficient or stable enough to implement effective sectoral strategies and policies that are part of an inclusive and sustainable economic growth pattern for all populations, particularly for women and girls.</narrative>
  </description>
